redshifts. Galactic disks are destroyed due to SN feedback, while galaxies in simulations with no feedback or lower SF efficiency models can sustain a galactic disk for long periods ? 10 \{Myr\}. The
expulsion of gas at the galactic center also affects the inner dark matter density profile for a short period. Our simulated galaxies in Halo-11 and Halo-12 reproduce the SF rates and stellar masses of observed Ly$\alpha$ emitters at z\~{} 7\{--\}8 fairly well given the
observational uncertainties.},
