	abstract = {Ly$\alpha$ halos are observed ubiquitously around star-forming galaxies 
at high redshift, but their origin is still a matter of debate. We
demonstrate that the emission from faint unresolved satellite sources,
\{M\}\{UV\}? -17, clustered around the central galaxies may
play a major role in generating spatially extended Ly$\alpha$, continuum
