out to z \~{} 3, comparable to the rise in H I and H2
fractions. Mufasa galaxies with high SFR at a given M* have lower metallicities and higher H I and H2 fractions,
following observed trends; we make quantitative predictions for how the fluctuations in the baryon cycle drive correlated scatter around galaxy scaling relations. Most of these trends are well converged with
