	abstract = {We introduce the BlueTides simulation and report initial results for the luminosity functions of the first galaxies and active galactic nuclei (AGN), and their contribution to reionization. BlueTides was run on the BlueWaters cluster at National Center for Super-computing Applications from z = 99 to 8.0 and includes 2 {\texttimes} 70403 particles in a 400 h-1 Mpc per side box, making it the largest
